1
00:00:04,900 --> 00:00:07,146
Faith will lead you 
to devotees.

2
00:00:07,146 --> 00:00:09,941
Sādhu-saṅga—
you’ll associate with them.

3
00:00:09,941 --> 00:00:12,959
In their association,
sādhau saṅgaḥ svato vare 
[Cc: 2.22.131]

4
00:00:12,959 --> 00:00:14,619
you’ll improve.

5
00:00:14,749 --> 00:00:17,740
[Converting Misconception 
Into Proper Conception]

6
00:00:17,980 --> 00:00:20,191
Your hankering will improve,

7
00:00:20,191 --> 00:00:24,221
it will shift,
paraḿ dṛṣṭvā nivartate 
[Bg: 2.59]

8
00:00:24,221 --> 00:00:29,603
You can start hankering 
for real, substantial things,

9
00:00:29,603 --> 00:00:31,116
just as you can hear:

10
00:00:31,116 --> 00:00:35,246
mach-chittā mad-gata-prāṇā …

11
00:00:35,246 --> 00:00:38,341
tuṣyanti cha ramanti cha
[Bg: 10.9]

12
00:00:38,341 --> 00:00:44,644
As deep, sensual an experience
can be in the mundane sense,

13
00:00:44,644 --> 00:00:47,782
it can be even deeper,
more intense,

14
00:00:47,782 --> 00:00:52,987
of greater intensity in magnitude
in the spiritual experience.

15
00:00:52,987 --> 00:00:55,913
But where 
will that be awakened?

16
00:00:57,081 --> 00:00:59,227
bhaktyā sañjātayā bhaktyā
[SB: 11.3.31]

17
00:00:59,227 --> 00:01:01,865
In association with those 
who have that.

18
00:01:02,375 --> 00:01:04,602
Sādhu-saṅga, bhajana-kriyā—

19
00:01:04,602 --> 00:01:07,851
under their direction;
they tell you what to do,

20
00:01:07,851 --> 00:01:10,307
how to make your approach.

21
00:01:10,307 --> 00:01:12,280
Anartha-nivṛtti—

22
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:18,257
misconception is gradually 
being converted into proper conception.

23
00:01:18,257 --> 00:01:23,345
Artha means 
in this sense ‘meaning’.

24
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:27,993
Anartha—‘the wrong idea’,
’the misconception’.

25
00:01:27,993 --> 00:01:33,038
Anartha-nivṛtti—that’s changing;
what we misconceived in the beginning

26
00:01:33,038 --> 00:01:39,201
is now shifting and moving
towards proper conception.

27
00:01:39,771 --> 00:01:48,171
Niṣṭhā. So, what was the laghu, light,
on the superficial soil,

28
00:01:48,171 --> 00:01:51,185
like the little plants
in the nursery,

29
00:01:51,201 --> 00:01:55,176
they can’t be put 
in the outside soil yet

30
00:01:55,176 --> 00:01:58,183
until they get some roots.

31
00:01:58,183 --> 00:02:00,657
When they become
deeply rooted,

32
00:02:00,657 --> 00:02:03,591
then they can be transplanted
to different environments

33
00:02:03,591 --> 00:02:06,822
and survive.
Not only survive, but thrive.

34
00:02:08,002 --> 00:02:14,657
So, the progressive
madhyam adhikārī devotee

35
00:02:14,657 --> 00:02:18,944
by converting misconception
to proper conception

36
00:02:18,944 --> 00:02:23,143
repeatedly
and in many varieties of ways,

37
00:02:23,143 --> 00:02:28,446
they get some strength 
and some insight,

38
00:02:30,276 --> 00:02:34,816
and some confidence 
to proceed.

39
00:02:36,708 --> 00:02:38,928
Niṣṭhā. Ruchi—

40
00:02:38,928 --> 00:02:44,741
then what was previously
being done out of obligation,

41
00:02:44,741 --> 00:02:47,678
the order of guru,

42
00:02:47,678 --> 00:02:50,379
sometimes even painfully,

43
00:02:50,379 --> 00:02:57,582
tapaḥ, voluntarily inconveniencing oneself
for the sake of the spiritual realisation,

44
00:02:57,582 --> 00:03:01,261
now there’s some actual taste
for those things.

45
00:03:01,261 --> 00:03:04,649
Likes to hear about Kṛṣṇa,

46
00:03:06,372 --> 00:03:08,332
nāma-gāne sadā ruchi 
[Cc: 2.23.32]

47
00:03:08,332 --> 00:03:14,248
likes, has some taste 
for the Holy Name.

48
00:03:16,465 --> 00:03:22,127
Ruchi. Then what? 
Āsakti, that’s attachment.

49
00:03:22,877 --> 00:03:27,067
So now being attached
to the right things,

50
00:03:27,067 --> 00:03:32,087
to spiritual things,
to spiritual association,

51
00:03:32,703 --> 00:03:36,182
it’s all right to transfer
our attachment to devotees,

52
00:03:36,182 --> 00:03:40,229
substantial devotees.
We want their association,

53
00:03:40,229 --> 00:03:46,218
we want to be in their association,
we hanker for their association.

54
00:03:48,757 --> 00:03:52,517
Bhāv, the bhāv-aṅkur—

55
00:03:52,517 --> 00:03:56,700
at this point the bhakti-latā-bīj
has sprouted, blossomed,

56
00:03:56,700 --> 00:04:03,639
and is flowering 
yielding a sweet fragrance

57
00:04:03,639 --> 00:04:08,019
that Kṛṣṇa finds pleasing.

58
00:04:08,619 --> 00:04:15,762
Kṛṣṇa actually is attracted to the devotion
that’s in the heart of that devotee,

59
00:04:15,762 --> 00:04:22,035
and that intensifies the bhāv,
produces the fruit—prem.

60
00:04:23,012 --> 00:04:25,281
Like that.

61
00:04:27,591 --> 00:04:30,151
Attached to sevā.

62
00:04:30,553 --> 00:04:32,453
Hare Kṛṣṇa

